  "target_response": {
    "text": "Both are real — they're different windows on the same metric. Your HRV is 63 ms: that's last night's single reading. Your 7-day average HRV is 65 ms: the same signal smoothed across the week, which is what trend views show. Day-to-day HRV is naturally noisy — hydration, a late meal, one restless hour can move it — so the averages are what's worth steering by. And right now the windows barely disagree: your HRV of 63 ms sits just under your 30-day average of 64.8 ms, well inside your normal spread. Nothing here needs action. The pattern that would actually mean something is the 7-day line drifting down for several consecutive days while resting heart rate climbs — one soft reading isn't that.",
